TRIAGE NOTES:
  HIGH:
    health.js:97
      probeAccount combines agent-specific auth path probing, secret-store persistence,
      token/JWT parsing, expiry derivation, and broad error conversion. Shared account
      health behavior is used by daemon/system health paths.

    paths.js:42
      resolveAuthPath mixes config precedence, platform/profile path construction,
      optional filesystem probing, and fallback errors. It is shared by account
      switching, health probing, auth capture, and UI IPC handlers.

    embeddings.js:41
      kMeans contains initialization, iterative assignment, centroid aggregation,
      empty-cluster handling, and final cluster construction. Algorithmic behavior
      is covered by tests but extraction must preserve clustering semantics.

    paths.js:151
      sanitizePathEntries is platform-sensitive security logic with allowlists,
      override handling, filesystem stat checks, and POSIX/Windows branches. Treat
      as HIGH despite +14 because the function gates spawned-process PATH safety.

  MED:
    training-exporter.js:32
      buildExportRecords groups documents, sorts pair sources, builds export rows,
      and applies quality filtering. Clear helper seams exist, but export shape is
      user-facing training data.

    check-sonar-readiness.mjs:25
      main loads governance artifacts, derives branch protection, accumulates
      failure reasons, and handles protected/non-protected exits. Script behavior
      affects governance gate status.

    test-bc2-integration.js:95
      runTests is a procedural integration-test runner with repeated result
      accounting and conditional sections. Test-only, but many observable messages
      and exit behavior sit in one function.

    encrypt.js:10
      getMachineId switches by platform and has multiple fallback probes before
      cached derivation. Security-adjacent and platform-sensitive.

    collector.js:208
      stageSignal validates several signal types, mutates diagnostic recurrence
      metadata, debounces, and updates buffers. Shared extension behavior and many
      tests cover this method.

    experience-db.js:381
      upsertDocuments builds dedupe state, appends rows, assigns IDs, and saves
      database state. Shared persistence surface; extraction must preserve uniqueBy
      semantics and chunk indexes.

    config.js:244
      loadConfig handles config read errors, strict/non-strict behavior, enterprise
      override loading, merge, schema validation, and fallback. Central startup
      surface with broad callers.

  LOW:
    idea-store.js:189
      listIdeas has a small excess from parse/quarantine/filter flow. Extraction
      can isolate file parsing/filter predicates without shared mutable state.

    document-ingester.js:366
      ingestFromSnapshot has a small excess from action planning and action
      execution. The two phases are clear and localized.

    plugin-loader.js:35
      loadPlugins has a small excess from plugin import/capability accumulation.
      Results arrays are local and helper extraction is straightforward.

    reporter.js:14
      Reporter.daily has a small excess from date normalization, file read fallback,
      journal line counting, and append. State is local to the method.

    browser-bridge.js:297
      launchBrowser has a +1 platform/browser branch for executable selection.
      Helper extraction around launch options should be narrow.

    handoff.js:100
      update command action has a +1 procedural command flow with local warnings
      and sprint mutation. Extracting option application is straightforward.

    inference.js:27
      findOllamaBinary has a +1 platform/env candidate selection branch. Local
      candidates array makes this a narrow helper extraction.

